This paper deals with the problem of generating faces from textual descriptions, which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also utilizes generative adversarial networks (GANs) and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for generating captions from attribute lists, which falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with image synthesis, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) research.
